tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE player_interactions (
    interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    player_id INT,
    interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
    interaction_description TEXT,
    interaction_timestamp TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE player_movements (
  movement_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  player_id INT,
  movement_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  movement_type VARCHAR(50),
  movement_direction VARCHAR(50),
  movement_speed FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE PlayerMovements (
    movement_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    player_id INT,
    movement_type VARCHAR(50),
    movement_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    movement_coordinates VARCHAR(100),
    movement_speed FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE VirtualRealityAnalysis (
    analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    player_id INT,
    analysis_type VARCHAR(50),
    analysis_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    analysis_result VARCHAR(200)
);

CREATE TABLE PlayerMovements (
	movement_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	player_id INT,
	movement_type VARCHAR(50),
	movement_time TIMESTAMP,
	location_x FLOAT,
	location_y FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE PlayerMovements (
    player_id INT,
    x_coordinate FLOAT,
    y_coordinate FLOAT,
    z_coordinate FLOAT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (player_id) REFERENCES PlayerInteractions(player_id)
);

CREATE TABLE InteractionLogs (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    player_id INT,
    interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
    FOREIGN KEY (player_id) REFERENCES PlayerInteractions(player_id)
);
